### Approach
1. **Sort the Array**: First, we sort the array in non-decreasing order. Sorting helps us easily access the smallest and largest elements during each step of the grouping process.
2. **Select Medians Efficiently**: After sorting, the largest elements are at the end of the array. For each group of three elements, we select one of the smallest remaining elements and two of the largest remaining elements. The median of such a group will be the second largest in the group, which corresponds to the smaller of the two largest elements selected.
3. **Sum the Medians**: We iterate through the array from the end, selecting every second element starting from the second last element (index `n-2`) and moving backwards by two steps each time. We sum these selected elements, which represent the medians of the groups formed, to get the maximum possible sum of medians.

### Solution Code
